# Techtribes Project Structure

This is a Jekyll-based website that lists tech community events worldwide. The main components are:

## Core Files

- [README.md](mdc:README.md) - Project overview and setup instructions
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Node.js dependencies and scripts
- [Gemfile](mdc:Gemfile) - Ruby dependencies for Jekyll

## Data Management

- [data/communities.yml](mdc:data/communities.yml) - Main data source for community listings
- [src/scrape.ts](mdc:src/scrape.ts) - Main scraping orchestration script
- [src/sort.ts](mdc:src/sort.ts) - Sorts communities alphabetically

## Scrapers

- [src/scrapers/](mdc:src/scrapers/) - Contains scrapers for different event platforms:
  - [meetup.ts](mdc:src/scrapers/meetup.ts) - Meetup.com scraper
  - [meetabit.ts](mdc:src/scrapers/meetabit.ts) - Meetabit scraper
  - [luma.ts](mdc:src/scrapers/luma.ts) - Luma scraper
  - [url.ts](mdc:src/scrapers/url.ts) - Generic URL scraper for custom APIs

## Site Generation

- [site/\_config.yml](mdc:site/_config.yml) - Jekyll configuration
- [site/\_layouts/default.html](mdc:site/_layouts/default.html) - Main HTML template
- [site/\_includes/](mdc:site/_includes/) - Reusable HTML components
- [site/assets/](mdc:site/assets/) - Static assets (CSS, images, logos)

## Key Scripts

- `npm run scrape` - Scrapes event data from all communities
- `npm run sort` - Sorts communities alphabetically
- `npm start` - Runs development server
- `npm run css` - Downloads and optimizes CSS
